						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Āpatsahāyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 3: 974 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva with the interest thereon, by Nakkaṉ Ariñjigai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Parāntaka-Pallava[raiyaṉ]. The gold was taken over by the <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> of Tiruppaḻaṉam.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 70.</p>						

